==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Branchiopoda
<hw>Bran"chi*o*poda</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/ gill + <ets>-poda</ets>: cf. F. <ets>branchiopode</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of Entomostraca; -- so named from the
feet of branchiopods having been supposed to perform the function of
gills. It includes the fresh-water genera <gen>Branchipus</gen>,
<gen>Apus</gen>, and <gen>Limnadia</gen>, and the genus
<gen>Artemia</gen> found in salt lakes. It is also called
<altname><ord>Phyllopoda</ord></altname>. See <er>Phyllopoda</er>,
<er>Cladocera</er>. It is sometimes used in a broader sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Branchiostegal</ent>⟦br⟧
